caption: Second time ordering from DoorDash and the delivery time has been impressive. The food is awesome! I grew up eating Thai food and so far, the dishes have delivered: chicken pad thai, pad see ew (ordered 2x), tofu panang curry, basil duck, pad woon sen, chicken laab, namsod, pineapple fried rice . . . all good!  More to come, but so far so good.

So I was kinda on the fence about ordering from here because I already have my preferred Thai food spot and because there aren’t many reviews on here... but it was late and my usual place wasn’t open. Anyway, I was pleasantly surprised! I ended up ordering two nights in a row. The massaman curry is so good! Such a simple recipe that you wouldn’t think it could be made bad (but to my horror, I’ve received it made with sweet potato before... so yeah), but the onions still had a little crunch and the potatoes were basically the potato version of “al dente”. The pad thai was delicious as well. Also, the second night ordering, they packed some free potstickers (which i actually ordered the first night and loved)!! I don’t know if maybe they recognized my doordash name or something, but either way it was just really sweet and made me get all mushy...  UPDATE: Just wanted to come back and say that I also tried their Pad Woonsen Glass Noodle dish.... and it’s so GOOD. Wanted to order for the 3rd night (I’m supporting my local business!!) but they’re closed.

This restaurant is a weeknight go-to. Delicious food, extremely friendly and welcoming staff, and wow they are fast with carry out orders! My favorites are the duck curry, the drunken noodles and the coconut bubble tea smoothie.

Looking for a local thai restaurant to support? This is the best local thai. You can tell all ingredients are fresh and each dish is unique, not your regular american thai restaurant.  Presentation is key here. It made me want the food even more. Also, the decor was on point so after covid, bring your significant other for date night!  The scallion crepes were very tasty but also very oily. Even though I liked the flavor, the oil was overboard.  The pineapple fried rice was delish! The serving was a mile high. The cashew chicken was very tasty and you could tell the difference in quality of ingredients. It tasted like your parent made it.  The duck... oh man... it was hands down the best dish. I don't even eat duck and it was scrumptious. I didn't have any bits of fat and the green beans were cooked yet still crisp, just the way I like them. The green beans bursted with flavor from the duck. Truly it was a 5 star dish in my books.  Did we stop there? No way. Thai tea ice cream and coconut ice cream for the table! They make them in house and I've now found the local place to go for unique, fresh ice cream.  Their takeout game is strong, so be sure to support them to try all of this deliciousness.
